        <h1 class="label">Biography</h1>
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>Anna was appointed Director (Communications) of the Scotland Office in December 2018. Following graduation from Glasgow University, Anna spent time in Japan and has worked for a number of government departments, including as a Special Adviser in the Home Office and as Deputy Director, Communications at Ofsted. She has also worked in the Mayor of Londonâ€™s press office and in the charity sector.</p>
</div>
      </section>

      <div class="current-roles" id="current-roles">
          <section class="role_appointment role" id="role_appointment_5269">
            <h1 id="deputy-director-communications">Deputy Director, Communications</h1>
            <div class="govspeak">
<p>The Deputy Director, Communications, is responsible for:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Advising ministers on communications matters</li>
  <li>Running an integrated and forward-looking communications team</li>
  <li>Communicating the activity of the department</li>
  <li>Working across the UK Government to support announcements and events in Scotland</li>
</ul>
</div>
